modules.description: This module provides operations for configuring JACK audio devices, including setting conversion quality, managing playback states, and handling buffer positions and latency. It works with audio data structures like device handles (`Bjack.t`) and supports control over volume settings, channel configurations, and buffer metrics such as frame sizes and bytes per second. Specific use cases include real-time audio processing, live performance setups, and low-latency audio applications requiring precise device tuning.
